This place is great for large groups and birthdays. My family had a table for 20(yes you read that correctly we had TWENTY PEOPLE). This restaurant: 1. took our large reservation and gave us a follow up  confirmation call for  our reservation 2 hours before our reservation the day of 2. had AWESOME customer service: very polite and answered all of our questions, helped us with menu choices 3. has a wonderful atmosphere: they play wonderful music in the back ground,  the lights at slightly dim and they have a lit tree of paradise (has little white lights on it),  white table linen, beautiful decor and cultural paintings, clean silverware and glassware,  clean restrooms, clean and clear floors 4. has wonderful and flavorful food: wonderful menu options-seafood, meats, EVEN NON-MEAT OPTIONS  ....the food is moist and flavorful, the menu has beautiful descriptions of the food 5. the prices are budget friendly: there is something for everyone's budget(small to big) on this menu 6. for birthdays they sing happy birthday to you and bring out a dessert  ***please know that it's hard to find parking in this area. There is a parking garage around the corner from the restaurant or you can find street parking, but space is tight and it is a busy surrounding area***  THIS RESTAURANT IS DEFINITELY WORTH GOING TO!

Long time institution in the Adams Morgan neighborhood. I've been coming here for years, and have never been disappointed. Be sure to ask your server for suggestions on potential dishes. I personally like their Seafood stews, which have lots of flavor and never fail to satisfy. Recent additions to the restaurant have added a lot of seating, making this a good choice even for larger groups.

I have dined at the Grill several times, since my arrival in the DMV about eight (8) months ago, and the food & staff have always been outstanding. The provençal fare is delightful departure from the standard churrascaria experience. There are several dishes I would recommend however, the seafood items are divine. The ambience is pleasing to the senses and the happy hour is outstanding. If you are worldy, then you will not be disappointed with Grill From Ipanima 😎
